    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 492.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 2, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> You will present to Mr. William Trater,
                            who presided over a meeting of the inhabitants of Galashiels held at the
                            Corn Exchange on the 5th of February last, the profound acknowledgments
                            of the President of the United States for the deep interest expressed by
                            the workingmen assembled on that occasion in behalf of the cause of the
                            United States in the painful domestic controversy in which they are now
                            unhappily engaged. The President hopes and confidently trusts that the
                            moral opinion of mankind, now happily awakened to the real nature and
                            character of the contest, will relieve it of every of its past
                            embarrassments, and be productive of benign results, favorable to the
                            interests of all nations.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
